$ .......
$ ...XX..
$ ..XXXX.
$ ..XXXX.
$ ...XX..
$ .......
≡⇌⊚=@X⇌⊜∘⊸≠@\n

Split  ← ⊕□>÷⊃⧻/+⊸◴⊢⊸⍉ # sort by x; find mid x; split.
Bridge ← ⊟∩⊣∩⍜≡⇌⍆°□₂   # find top in both; couple.
Top    ← ⊣⊏⍏⊣⊸⍉        # highest y-value.

# TopHull: if all same X, just return top one;
# if size <= 2 return it/them; else split, bridge and recurse.
TopHull ← |1 ⍣(Top°1⧻◴⊢⊸⍉|∘°1≤2⊸⧻|⊂⊂⊙(∩TopHull°□₂)⊸Bridge Split)
# Do once normally; once for negated version; join; dedup.
◴⊂×₋₁∩TopHull⊸×₋₁

